      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CAMERINA (3) looks ready to win having finished runner-up in both starts so far this campaign. Turned in yet another strong performance last start when she came from this barrier and battled on bravely to be beaten less than 2m at Kilmore. Race fit and is likely to get the favours from this draw so could break through. DARLINGTON (5) is stepping out for the first time. By good sire Sweet Lou and hails from the Jess Tubbs stable. Placed in a recent trial at this venue. Should be well educated and could kick off with a win. MAJOR ORION (4) must be considered after placing in both starts so far, last week coming from wider for third at Bendigo. WALKWITHME (8) is a three-year-old filly by Art Major on debut. Looked above average in winning the latest trial and draws for a trail so keep safe.",
